## 5. What Problems Security & Compliance Solves

Security & Compliance should be understood through the problems it addresses in real environments.

### 5.1 Risk exposure in production environments

Studios and production teams handle sensitive, unreleased content that requires strong protection across systems, users, and workflows.

### 5.2 Difficulty meeting compliance requirements

Frameworks such as TPN introduce requirements that many organizations are not fully prepared to meet without structured support.

### 5.3 Security controls that disrupt workflows

Security measures can slow teams down when they are not designed with production realities in mind.

### 5.4 Lack of visibility into vulnerabilities

Organizations may not have a clear view of where risks exist across infrastructure, endpoints, and workflows.

### 5.5 Fragmented security across tools and environments

Production environments often include multiple systems, vendors, and locations, making consistent security difficult to maintain.

### 5.6 Scaling challenges as production grows

Security requirements become more complex as teams expand, collaborate externally, or adopt hybrid workflows.

