## 6. Core Capabilities of GPL Security & Compliance

Security & Compliance at GPL combines three interconnected capability areas: security operations, compliance alignment, and production-aware implementation.

### 6.1 Security Operations

This capability focuses on protecting environments at a technical level.

It includes:

* infrastructure hardening
* endpoint protection
* access control and identity management
* vulnerability assessment and remediation
* monitoring and alerting
* ongoing risk management

This layer supports the stability and protection of day-to-day operations.

---

### 6.2 Compliance & Framework Alignment

This capability focuses on helping organizations meet external requirements and standards.

It includes:

* TPN readiness and support
* audit preparation
* policy development and alignment
* control implementation
* documentation support
* gap assessments and remediation planning

This layer ensures organizations can demonstrate that their environments meet required standards.

---

### 6.3 Production-Aware Security Implementation

This capability ensures that security measures align with how teams actually work.

It includes:

* designing controls that fit real production workflows
* securing collaboration between internal teams and external partners
* protecting content across distributed environments
* aligning security with production timelines
* minimizing friction while maintaining protection

This layer is what differentiates GPL from generic security providers.

